<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Oil Refinery Resumes Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 29 (Xinhua) (C The Tanzania-Italian
Petroleum Refinery (TIPER) has resumed production following
availability of crude oil.
</P>
<P>
TIPER halted production early this month because the importer,
Tanzania Petroleum Development Corporation (TPDC) had problems in
securing a letter of credit from its bank in favor of the
supplier.
</P>
<P>
Yona Kilagane, the managing director of TPDC, the supplier,
said in Dar es Salaam Thursday that TIPER has recently received
86,000 tons of crude oil estimated at 12 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Kilagane said TPDC has sorted out the financial issues with its
 banker late last week and that ultimately the letter of credit
was opened in favor of Messrs Addax of Switzerland that supplied
the crude oil.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the fate of privatizing TIPER, which is capable of
processing 650,000 tons of oil annually, will be known before the
end of this year under the policy of liberalizing the oil
industry, sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
