<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Rebuilding and expansion of the
Pristina airport in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo will start in
August, the Interfax news agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
NATO member countries have allocated 6 million U.S. dollars for
the he project, which will take two to three years, Interfax said,
quoting an official of the Russian Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
