<HEADLINE> Two Tanzanian Airlines to Cooperate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Air Tanzania Corporation
(ATC), the country's national airline, signed an agreement here
Thursday with a domestic private firm Precision Air.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by ATC acting managing director
Emmanuel Kimaro and Precision Air director Michael Shirima.
</P>
<P>
ATC marketing director Mohamed Mzee said that under the
agreement his company has allowed some of its routes to be used
by the Precision Air.
</P>
<P>
To start with, Precision Air will work together with ATC on
three routes, namely Mwanza in north Tanzania to Kenyan capital
Nairobi, northern region of Kilimanjaro to Nairobi, and Kenyan
port city Mombasa to Kilimanjaro, he said.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation is scheduled to start in September this year,
he said. 
</P>
