<HEADLINE> Four Zambian Miners Feared Dead in Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Four miners are feared dead
following an underground mine accident at Zambia Consolidated
Copper Mines (ZCCM) Nchanga division Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened in the morning and by four in the
afternoon rescue workers were still battling to find the four
miners who are trapped in their working tunnels at Nchanga's only
shaft number one.
</P>
<P>
ZCCM manager for corporate affairs, Sam Equamo, has confirmed
the accident but could not give further details.
</P>
<P>
"Yes, I can confirm that a mine accident has occurred at
Nchanga division and four workers are feared dead. Rescue workers
are trying to find them," Equamo said in a press statement.
</P>
<P>
ZCCM Nchanga division has an open pit and shaft but the
accident took place at the shaft.
</P>
<P>
Unconfirmed report reaching Zambia News Agency said the cause
of the accident was mud rash similar to the one which occurred at
ZCCM Mufulira division some twenty years ago.
</P>
<P>
It is said that a large quantity of mud on surface of the mine
trickled into the mine shaft and into the tunnel where the four
miners were working and trapped them.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, a similar accident occurred at the same mine in which
four other miners lost their lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
