<DOCNO> XIE19990730.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 24 Injured in Clashes Between Police, Public Servants in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Some 24 persons were injured
Thursday when police and government employees clashed at the
Bangladesh Secretariat in central Dhaka, paralyzing the normal
work for nearly three hours.
</P>
<P>
The government employees staged a demonstration from 10 a.m. to
1 p.m. at the secretariat, where the ministries are located, to
press home their demand including changing of the present office
timing and enhancement of economic benefits, sources said.
</P>
<P>
A heavy contingent of police were deployed at the secretariat,
and at one point, clashes occurred between the police and the
demonstrators, injuring 24 people, including four policemen and 20
government employees.
</P>
<P>
The employees' leaders have announced a fresh course of action
on August 3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
