<HEADLINE> Regional Summit of Stability Pact Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sarajevo, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of states and governments
from Balkan region opened first day summit of Stability Pact for
southeastern Europe on Thursday in Sarajevo, the capital of Bosnia
and Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was opened by Martti Ahtisaari, the Finnish
president who is also the current president of the European Union.
</P>
<P>
The Balkan leaders are trying to set out their priorities for
the region before the full-scale summit starts on Friday, which
will be attended by some 40 world leaders.
</P>
<P>
The Thursday's summit was attended by the leaders from Albania,
Bugaria, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Hungary, Romania,
Slovenia, Switzerland, Turkey, Former Yugoslavia republic of
Macedonia and some international organizations.
</P>
<P>
According to press office here, about 1,960 journalists are
covering this event. 
</P>
