<HEADLINE> Luneng Taishan Beat Shenhua in Top of Table Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Luneng Taishan enlarged their lead
to three points after beating Shanghai Shenhua 1-0 in a top of the
table match in the 16th round of the Chinese first division soccer
league on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai team, which lost the top position after suffering
their first defeat of the season last Sunday, dominated the match
from the start. But they could not tear off the defense line of
Luneng Taishan.
</P>
<P>
Luneng Taishan concentrated on defense and took chance to
launch counter-attack. Their efforts paid off at the 25th minute
when Song Lihui headed home the winner.
</P>
<P>
The win consolidated Luneng Taishan's lead in the league with
31 points, three points more than second-placed Chongqing Longxin
which beat Guangzhou Songri 3-0 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Fushun jumped to the third place after winning their
tie against Shenyang Haishi 3-1.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Dalian Wanda, boosted by the return of Sun
Jihai from England first division team Crystal Palace, scored
their third consecutive win, beating Shenzhen Ping'an 2-0.
</P>
<P>
In Thursday's other matches, Beijing Guo'an beat Wuhan Heart K
6-0, Tianjin Taida beat Jilin Aodong 3-1, Qingdao Hainiu drew with
Sichuan Quanxing 1-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
