<HEADLINE> Clinton Leaves for Balkan Rebuilding Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 29 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
left here Wednesday for Sarajevo, the capital of Bosnia, to attend
an international conference on the Balkans rebuilding scheduled on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The White House said that Clinton will persuade the western
powers to strengthen the isolation of Yugoslavia's leader Slobodan
Milosevic.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Secretary of State Madeleine Albright and
National Security Advisor Sandy Berger, Clinton will join leaders
of nearly 40 nations to discuss a new Marshall Plan for
southeastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
They will also assess the costs of rebuilding Kosovo and
stabilizing its neighbors following the 78-day air campaign
against Yugoslavia by the U.S.-led NATO.  
</P>
