<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Forex Deficit Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's foreign exchange market
suffered a set-back this week on the back of increased demand, the
country's central bank said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Reserve Bank of Zimbabwe said in its weekly report that the
market took a serious knock this week when the forex deficit rose
from 1.7 million U.S. dollars on July 22 to 6.5 million U.S.
dollars on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts said demand was outstripping supply as everyone
had been looking forward to the release of 200 million U.S.
dollars balance of payment support from the International Monetary
Fund (IMF) by the end of July. The money is now expected after
mid August, the Zimbabwe News Agency reported.  
</P>
</TEXT>
