<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Legal System Can Not Be Damaged by Falun Gong: Officials and People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Officials and people from all
walks of life of the country stressed today that the great
achievement made in China's construction of socialist legal system
will not allow to be damaged by Falun Gong or other superstitious
activities.
</P>
<P>
We will never allow Li Hongzhi and the illegal Falun Gong
attempts to destroy the building of China's socialist legal system,
they said.
</P>
<P>
Police officers in Tianjin Municipality said that preventing
Falun Gong practitioners from receiving medical treatment in
hospitals impinges on people's rights, and the attack and siege of
news media units and governmental departments violate legal
regulations on demonstrations.
</P>
<P>
A civil administration official in east China's Shandong
Province said that the Research Society of Falun Dafa acted
against the law on the registration of associations, and the
illegal organization was never approved by related authority.
</P>
<P>
Li developed a tight organization system in Beijing and many
other parts of the country, the official said, and this violated
the law and the ban on organizations that spread superstitious
fallacies and destroy social stability.
</P>
<P>
The ban ensures the people's natural rights to life and health,
and guarantees a normal social order. This demonstrates China's
policy insisting on managing state affairs in accordance with laws
and developing a socialist country with a legal system.
</P>
<P>
Employees of publishers in east China's Anhui Province have
noted that the books and materials on Falun Gong are full of
superstitious fallacies and pseudo-science, and Li and his
followers printed these illegal publications for sale at high
prices for quick and huge profits.
</P>
<P>
They stressed that the knowledge of law should be further
spread among ordinary people to help them spurn fatuity and see
the true face of Li and the illegal Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
The People's Daily and the Guangming Daily today jointly hosted
a seminar attended by a group of Beijing-based scholars who
criticized Falun Gong from the perspective of politics, theory,
philosophy, science, and medicine.
</P>
<P>
They strongly condemned the political nature and great harm of
Li Hongzhi and the Falun Dafa he concocted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
