<HEADLINE> Results at European Swimming Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISTANBUL, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Following are the finals results
at the 24th European Swimming Championships here on Thursday:
</P>
<P>
Women's 200 meters individual medley:
</P>
<P>
1. Yana Klochkova, Ukraine, 2:14.02
</P>
<P>
2. Beatrice Caslaru, Romania, 2:15.12
</P>
<P>
3. Sabine Klenz, Germany, 2:16.95
</P>
<P>
4. Annika Mehlhorn, Germany, 2:17.82
</P>
<P>
5. Lourdes Becerra, Spain, 2:19.40
</P>
<P>
6. Katia Sarakatsani, Greece, 2:19.54
</P>
<P>
7. Rachael Corner, Britain, 2:19.92
</P>
<P>
8. Alenka Kejzar, Slovenia, 2:21.53
</P>
<P>
Men's 50 meters backstroke:
</P>
<P>
1. Stev Theloke, Germany, 25.66 (European record)
