<HEADLINE> U.N. Warns of Locust Infestation in Parts of CIS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 29 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Food and
Agriculture Organization (FAO) Thursday issued a special alert to
locusts infestations into areas of Russia from Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Locust swarms have also spread into Uzbekistan and Kyrgyzstan,
said the FAO.
</P>
<P>
It said that the situation is serious as both farmers and the
government in all the affected countries lack adequate resources
and technology to deal effectively with the problem.
</P>
<P>
The locusts, which have already caused damage to crops in
Kazakhstan and Russia, have laid eggs over millions of hectares
with the possibility of hatching in the next spring, posing a
greater threat to next year's crops, the Rome-based agency warned.
</P>
