<HEADLINE> Annan Sends Message to Sarajevo Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, July 30 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Secretary General
Kofi Annan said on Friday that the Stability Pact Summit taking place
in Sarajevo today marks a new beginning in the efforts of the
international community to end the Balkan wars of this century.
</P>
<P>
The UN chief delivered the message through Carl Bildt, his special
Balkan envoy. "After a decade of conflict that has taken us from
Croatia and Bosnia to Kosovo, we have now returned to Sarajevo with
a strong determination to achieve lasting peace," he said.
</P>
<P>
"With this meeting, and with the extraordinary attention and
dedication devoted to overcoming the devastating results of the last
of the Balkan wars, the international community has the opportunity
to honor its pledges towards this region, and thereby enable the
peoples of the region to achieve stability in their own lives,"
said Annan who did not attend the Sarajevo summit.
</P>
<P>
He said the Sarajevo meeting will give all efforts of the United
Nations "new inspiration and new initiative" so that "we enter the
new century with renewed faith in lasting peace and prosperity for
the entire region".
</P>
<P>
Leaders from major western countries and Balkan nations and heads
of main international organizations ended the Stability Pact Summit
this afternoon after issuing a Declaration calling for integration of
Balkans into a single European model.
</P>
<P>
The stability pact was initiated and adopted by the European Union,
and agreed in principle by the leaders who participated in the summit.
</P>
<P>
The leaders said in their final declaration that they "welcome and
support the appointment of Mr. Bodo Hombach as the Special Coordinator
of the Stability Pact by the Council of the European Union, as
endorsed by the Chairman in Office of the OSCE (Organization of
Security and Cooperation in Europe)".
</P>
<P>
"We pledge our full cooperation to the Special Coordinator in the
achievement of our objectives," they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
