<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts Seminar Condemning  Lee Teng-hui's "Two-States" Statement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A seminar, attended by members of
the Beijing Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), members of Democratic Parties,
persons with no party affiliation, and representatives of Beijing-
based Taiwan compatriots, was held here today to condemn Lee Teng-
hui's separatist "two-states" statement.
</P>
<P>
They noted that Taiwan authorities must immediately stop
separatists activities and back to the policy of adhering to the "
One China" principle.
</P>
<P>
Xia Chao, deputy-director of the subcommittee of Hong Kong,
Macao, Taiwan, and Overseas Chinese Affairs of the CPPCC Beijing
Committee, pointed out that under the pressure of the
international communities, Lee has now begun using deception in an
attempt to cover his true nature.
</P>
<P>
Sophism just will not save Lee Teng-hui, nor can the Chinese
people at home and abroad be fooled, he said, adding that the only
way for Lee Teng-hui is to abandon the "two-states" statement and
resume the policy of adhering to the "One China" principle.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Weiying, associate professor at People's University in
Beijing, said that Lee's separatist remarks act against not only
the principle on a sovereign state according to law of nations,
but also the local law of Taiwan, which is based on the "One China
" policy.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jinfeng, a native of Taiwan who returned to the mainland
in the 1980s, said that more and more people in Taiwan are
realizing Lee's true nature as a separatist. Zhang believes that
the majority of Taiwan people maintain the tradition of patriotism
and desire China's peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Su Minsheng, vice chairman of the All-China Federation of
Taiwan Compatriots, and many other seminar participants, noted
that further strengthening of exchanges and cooperation across the
Straits is the common will of both the Chinese people in the
mainland and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
They emphasized that the Chinese government intends to resolve
the issue of Taiwan in a timely manner. Attempts to split Taiwan
from the motherland will never prevail, Chinese territory and
sovereignty can never be separated, and the cause of China's unity
can never be damaged.  
</P>
</TEXT>
