<HEADLINE> Italian Duo Win Men's 3m Springboard Synchronised Diving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISTANBUL, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Donald Miranda and Nicola Marconi
won Italy their first European diving title since 1974 when they
took the gold of men's 3 meters springboard synchronised diving on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Miranda and Marconi, bronze medallists in Seville in 1997, beat
German defending champions Alexander Mesch and Holger Schlepps in
a close final. Britain's Antonio Ali and Mark Shipman took the
bronze medal.
</P>
<P>
The Italian duo compiled 303.24 points while the Germans had
299.79. The British pair were at 296.01. 
</P>
