<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Falun Gong Has Tight Organization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A recent investigation by the
Chongqing Public Security Bureau in southwest China's Chongqing
Municipality shows that Falun Gong is a well-organized and fast-
acting illegal cult.
</P>
<P>
The organization of Falun Gong in Chongqing has five layers:
the general station, sub-branches, first-level instruction centers,
second-level instruction centers, and exercising centers.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi, founder of Falun Gong, appointed the head of the
general station who named his two deputies.
</P>
<P>
The general station has three sub-branches, each with a
director and an executive deputy director.
</P>
<P>
The three sub-branches have 56 first- and second-level
instruction centers, and 890 exercising centers. The five layers
of organization have 358 leaders, and each layer has its own
division of work, the investigation reveals.
</P>
<P>
Falun Gong practitioners have besieged some news media
organizations in Chongqing on many occasions beginning last year.
All these activities were under the control of the Li Hongzhi's
Falun Dafa Research Society (FDRS) in Beijing and instigated and
directly led by the general station in Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The investigation proves that the dispatch and deployment of
local Falun Gong practitioners and their final retreat were
organized by the Chongqing general station and the FDRS in Beijing
through instructions sent via phone calls and faxes.
</P>
<P>
Under such tight organization, Falun Gong followers are easily
made use of by Li Hongzhi, said a senior official of the Chongqing
Public Security Bureau.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
