<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia's Population Continues to Decrease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Russia's population continued to
decrease this year, with a drop of 346,700 in the first five
months, the Interfax news agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The population is estimated at 146 million as of July 1.
</P>
<P>
The number of new births in January-May dropped to 507,300 as
against 531,100 during the same period last year. The number of
deaths increased from 844,400 to 903,000 in the period under
review.
</P>
<P>
The number of marriages posted a slight increase during the
period from 273,200 to 275,600. The number of divorces dropped
from 228,700 to 208,500, Interfax said, quoting the State
Statistics Service.
</P>
<P>
Fewer people entered Russia during the five months. A total of
134,000 people arrived in Russia from abroad compared to 202,000
in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
More people were leaving Russia as 80,700 left the country
compared to 72,700 in the same period last year. In effect, the
net increase due to migration, at 53,300, dropped to just over 40
percent from last year's figure of 129,300.
</P>
<P>
Valentina Matviyenko, deputy prime minister in charge of
social affairs, said Friday that the population decline, though
still grave, would not threaten Russia's national survival and
would stop in the coming years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
