<DOCNO> XIE19990730.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Efforts to Ban Falun Gong &AMP; Safeguard Stability Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A commentary released here today
by the Xinhua News Agency said that only by outlawing illegal
organizations in accordance with law can social and political
stability be achieved and the interests of the overwhelming
majority of Chinese be safeguarded.
</P>
<P>
Facts have demonstrated that the Falun Gong organization
controlled by Li Hongzhi is a tightly organized cult, the
commentary said, its supreme organ in China is the Falun Dafa
Research Society (FDRS) in Beijing. Under the FDRS, there are 39
general stations, 1,900 instruction centers, and 28,000 exercising
sites. Li Hongzhi sent his instructions through these general
stations, instructions centers, and exercising sites.
</P>
<P>
However, this large and tightly run organization failed to go
through any legitimate registration procedures. Therefore, it has
violated China's Constitution and the regulation on citizen
associations, the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
The illegal activities of Falun Gong such as spreading
superstition and stirring up disturbances have also violated the
country's regulation that social organizations should abide by the
Constitution and avoid harming the interests of the State and
deviating from social morality, the commentary concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
