<HEADLINE> German Wins Women's 100m Backstroke </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISTANBUL, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Sandra Voelker of Germany won the
women's 100 meters backstroke title at the European Swimming
Championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Voelker, who lost her 100 meters freestyle title to Sue Rolph
of Britain on Wednesday, took the gold with a time of one minute 1.
39 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Fastest final qualifier Nina Zhivanevskaya of Spain, who won a
silver in 1993 and bronze in 1995 when she represented Russia,
took the silver at 1:01.98.
</P>
<P>
Romanian-born Roxana Maracineanu of France, the reigning world
and European 200 backstroke champion, took the bronze in 1:02.47.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Antje Buschschulte of Germany finished a
disappointing fifth. 
</P>
