<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Team Halti Claims Outdoor Quest Lead (Corrected) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALI, China, July 30 (Xinhua) -- On a day when athletes learned
the true spirit of adventuring racing, Team Halti took the lead
here at the Mild Seven Outdoor Quest on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Every team but Halti -- a team highly experienced in offroad
navigation -- missed a crucial turnaround point during the run
course. Halti was still awarded the stage victory, but the run
section of the race was excluded from total race standings.
</P>
<P>
"we regret the error in course making," Executive Race Director
Nick Freyer said in a post-race statement. "It would not happen
again."
</P>
<P>
The decision of Freyer and race director Murphy Reinschreiber
was that Day Two competition officially ended after the opening
mountain bike biathlon and offroad inline skating phases --
roughly two-and-a-half hours of intense racing.
</P>
<P>
With two days to go, a half-dozen teams stand a legitimate
chance of claiming victory when the event concludes on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Team Eco-Internet, who won the first-day competition on
Thursday, stood second with nine minutes behind Halti. Team Red
Bull-Buff of Spain is third.
</P>
<P>
Team Mild Seven, the top Chinese squad bounced back from a
disappointing showing on Day One and came seventh overall at 9:32:
48. Their incredible cycling, running and paddling skills mean
they stand in solid position to catch the leaders during Day Three
's 12 hours of competition.
</P>
<P>
Beginning at the majestic South Gate of Dali, teams competed in
a blazing-fast mountain bike biathlon leg, then switched into
offroad inline skates for another intense stage inside the Old
City.
</P>
<P>
Team Halti opened up a six-minute lead over Eco-Internet,
completely erasing a five-minute deficit from the opening day.
</P>
<P>
Shedding their skates, they quickly began another grueling
mountain bike biathlon stage that took athletes out of Dali to the
shores of Lake Erhai. From there, the plan of race organizers was
for athletes to leave their bikes behind and head up into the
mountains for 15 kilometers of trail running.
</P>
<P>
In traditional adventure racing, courses are not marked and
contestants depend on map and compass skills to navigate. But Mild
Seven Outdoor Quest officials prefer to keep the emphasis on pure
endurance competition and thus rigorously mark their courses.
</P>
<P>
While Halti had read the maps studiously prior to beginning Day
Two, other teams had not. So While Halti did the proper thing and
turned around at the crucial moment several kilometers into the
run, other teams did not. Rather than penalize teams for
continuing on the course, race organizers accepted all blame and
disallowed the run section of the course.
</P>
<P>
Halti, which saw their lead reduced from 37 minutes to nine,
took the news well. "We are all very tired now, " Halti's Mika
Hirvinen said. "We liked it a lot -- the scenery, the mental
challenge -- but it was very, very hard today. Right now we have
to put this behind and move on, because Day Three will be very
difficult." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990730.0090 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 67 Percent Nigerians Below Poverty Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Poverty level in Nigeria has jumped
to a worrisome rate of 67 percent of its population from the 1960
figure of 22 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Post Express newspaper Friday quoted government official as
saying that no concerted efforts had really been made in tackling
the roots of poverty by previous governments in the country
despite their various ad hoc policies and programs.
</P>
<P>
Alhaji Joda, chairman of the Presidential Panel on Streamlining
and Rationalization of Poverty Alleviation Institutions and
Agencies, also lamented in Ibadan, capital of Nigeria's Oyo
state Thursday that the drastic reduction in the standard of
living arises from people's inability to get good food, potable
water, education, medical facilities and high rate of
unemployment.
</P>
<P>
According to Joda, who is on a working trip in the state, it
was in view of the array of problems in the society that President
Olusegun Obasanjo decided to set up the panel "so as to address
and coordinate solutions in a fashionable way."
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the determination of the present
administration to provide basic social amenities for the benefit
of the masses.
</P>
<P>
Oyo state Governor Lam Adesina, when talking with him, remarked
that no poverty alleviation program put in place by the federal
government would yield its desired result until the state
governments are given their equitable shares of the Federation
Account.
</P>
<P>
He said Nigerians would continue to be impoverished if the
federal government continued to hold on to the lion's share of the
Federation Account and give only pittance to the states.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria has dropped from the list of world's top 50 richest
countries into the poorest 20 since its independence in 1960.
It's widely believed that rampant corruption and mis-management
of its economy lie in the root of the west African country's
deepening poverty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
