<HEADLINE> Ukraine Swimmer Wins Men's 1,500m Freestyle Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISTANBUL, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Igor Snitko of Ukraine scored a
convincing victory to take the title of the men's 1,500 meters
freestyle at the European Swimming Championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Snitko, silver medalist in the last edition of the
championships in Seville in 1997, took the lead from German Joerg
Huenecke in the second 100 meters and was never challenged in his
quest for the gold.
</P>
<P>
Snitko's winning time stands at 15 minutes 7.19 seconds.
Romania's Dragan Coman, who won the 400m freestyle bronze medal on
Monday, took the silver in 15:13.10.
</P>
<P>
Sylvain Cros of France took the bronze in 15:18.26. Former
world champion Joerg Hoffmann of Germany, who won this title four
times between 1989 and 1995, could not hold his pace in the race
and finished fifth at 15:24.94. 
</P>
