<HEADLINE> Beijing's New Vice Mayor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
Beijing Municipal People's Congress today elected Liu Zhihua as a
vice mayor in charge of the Zhongguancun High-Tech Park.
</P>
<P>
The 50-year-old Liu worked with the Bureau of Labor from 1982
to 1989, and then transferred to the Ministry of Labor until 1994.
He is now Secretary-General of the Beijing Municipal People's
Government.
</P>
<P>
According to Beijing Mayor Liu Qi, Liu Zhihua has always
concentrated on modern technology and market economy theory and
related policies. Liu is also outstanding for his extraordinary
ability to organize and cooperate with others.
</P>
<P>
Among Beijing's mayor and nine vice mayors, seven have
postgraduate degrees, and one of the two female vice mayors is a
professor who is an advisor to doctorate postgraduates at Qinghua
University.  
</P>
</TEXT>
