<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most Chinese Cities Report Good Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Most Chinese cities had good air
quality this week, with none reporting medium or serious air
pollution, according to the China Environmental Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
From July 23 to 30, parts of country had rainfall, which helped
eliminate pollutants in the air.
</P>
<P>
Guilin, Shenzhen, Ningbo, Wenzhou, Fuzhou, Suzhou, Haikou, and
Xiamen reported excellent air quality during the period, while
Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou, Kunming, Shenyang, Wuhan and other
26 cities reported good air quality.
</P>
<P>
Hohhot, Taiyuan, Yinchuan, Xi'an, and Zhengzhou in the north
and northwest, reported slight air pollution, mostly from an
excess of suspended particles.  
</P>
</TEXT>
