<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gale Storm Claims 18 Lives in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 30 (Xinhua) -- At least 18 people were killed and
477 injured in a gale storm on July 28 in southwest China's
Sichuan Province, which also resulted in economic losses of 340
million yuan (about 41 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to the latest report from the provincial government,
most parts of Sichuan were hit by moderate to strong gales,
coupled with hail and rainstorms in some areas, two days ago,
affecting 4.3 million people in 16 cities and 50 counties across
the province.
</P>
<P>
The disaster also destroyed 200,000 houses, and 6,500 meters of
electric lines. At the same time, the gale hit 220,000 hectares of
crop land, causing the loss of 43 million kilos of grain, said a
local official.
</P>
<P>
Fortunately, because of timely forecasts a few hours before the
storm, governments in a number of cities discharged some 1,800
shells to dissipate the hailstone clouds, considerably decreasing
losses, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
