Friday on the Karachi Stock Exchange amid optimism that the
long-standing power tariff issue between the government and the
Independent Power Producers (IPP) would be solved through
dialogue.
</P>
<P>
The key market indicator, 100-share price index, surged 26.22
points, or 2.13 percent, from Thursday's 1,225.57 points to close
the week at 1,251.79 points as investors grabbed blue chip stocks.
</P>
<P>
The total volume traded Friday also rose to 202.989 million
shares against Thursday's 145.332 million shares.
</P>
