<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Greets 7 Millionth Passenger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Macao International Airport
greeted its seven millionth passenger on Friday since its opening
on November 9, 1995, a press release of the airport said.
</P>
<P>
The airport saw passenger traffic grow by 24 percent in the
first half of this year over the same period of 1998, according to
the press release.
</P>
<P>
A total of 11 regular airline companies link the airport with
24 cities worldwide, 16 of which are located in the mainland areas
of China. Air routes to China's Guilin, Xi'an and Kunming cities
were opened not long ago.
</P>
<P>
The airport has handled over 71,000 flights and 164,000 tons of
air cargo in the three and a half years since it opened. It
targets a passenger volume of 2.5 million in 1999. 
