<DOCNO> XIE19990730.0123 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Produces More Farm-Use Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China churned out 1.5 million farm-use vehicles during the half-
year period, up 8.52 percent on a yearly basis, and the production-
sales rate hit 99.92 percent, according to statistics of the China
Agricultural Machinery Industry Association.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, four-wheel farm-use vehicles hit 272,767, a
drastic increase of 12.2 percent, while three-wheel vehicles
increased 7.79 percent to chalk up 1.3 million.
</P>
<P>
Though the sector registered a 0.6-percent rise in total output
value, which stood at more than 12.7 billion yuan (1.53 billion U.
S. dollars) in the first half of this year, many enterprises
suffered losses in profits because of a slide in prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
