<HEADLINE> China Life, CMG to Form Joint Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- China Life Insurance Company and
Austrilian financial services company Colonial Mutual Group (CMG),
announced here today that they had signed a contract to form a
joint venture life insurance company in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The projected joint venture has been approved by the State
Council and the China Insurance Regulatory Commission (CIRC), said
a joint media release faxed to Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture is expected to commence operation within the
next half year.
</P>
<P>
Chairman and President of the China Life, He Jiesheng said the
joint venture is the culmination of many years' hard work and long-
standing co-operation between the two organizations.
</P>
<P>
"China Life has chosen CMG as its partner because of its
extensive international insurance expertise, particularly its
strong track record of success operating joint venture insurance
businesses in Asia," she said.
</P>
<P>
CMG's Group Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer Peter
Smedley said that CMG is honored to join China Life, China's
largest insurance company, to form the joint venture.
</P>
<P>
"CMG's worldwide business has achieved strong growth and
profitability. We look forward to achieving the same success in
China in conjunction with our partner," he said.
</P>
<P>
The proposed joint venture would be known as China Life CMG and
would have a registered capital of 200 million yuan, with China
Life contributing 51 percent and CMG 49 percent, the release said.
</P>
<P>
China Life is the sole state-owned commercial life insurance
company in China. It boasts a total asset of 90 billion yuan and
an annual premium income of 50 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The company now has 3,400 branches and offices throughout China
and employs 43,000 staff.
</P>
<P>
CMG is a diverse international financial services group with
core business in insurance, pensions, funds management and banking.
It has a presence in 12 markets and employs 28,000 staff and
distributors around the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
