<HEADLINE> China's Railway Passengers Increasing in Summer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The number of China's railway
passengers has significantly increased since July 1 when the
country's summer railway transportation period started and
numerous travelers began their tours across the country.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that the railway department has
carried 56.2 million passengers during July 1-20, up 11.3 percent
compared to the same period last year. The number on July 20 even
hit three million, the highest for the 20 days.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the darpartment's daily ticket income
averaged 98.2 million yuan, 6.8 million yuan more than expected.
The daily income in nine days even exceeded 100 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
China has officially defined the summmer transportation period
this year from July 1 to August 31, when 170 million passengers
are expected to be carried, up five percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
According to related insiders, the number of railway
passengers has steadily increased since this year, which indicates
that market-oriented efforts made by the country's railway
department over the past two years has gradually taken effect.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
