<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed on
Singapore Stock Market Friday as the market took a breather after
rising sharply on better corporate earnings and Singapore's
favorable economic situation.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) was 0.93 points lower
to close at 2,145.77 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume was 560.03 million shares worth 807.69 million
Singapore dollars (475.11 million U.S. dollars). Gainers
outnumbered losers by 207 to 120 with 120 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
AFP topped the volume list with a turnover of 20.02 million
units. It was followed by GoldenAg which had 18.04 million shares
done. Amara was the next with 17.94 million counters changing
hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH headed the ascent of the day running up 80 cents to close
at 29.80 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 ran up 70 cents to finish at
29.90 Singapore dollars. CityDev gained 40 cents to end at 11.70
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser giving up 70
cents to close at 17.60 Singapore dollars. OUB F shed 40 cents to
finish at 8.10 Singapore dollars. OCBC retreated 20 cents to end
at 12.60 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the Wall Street's overnight fall dampened the
market sentiment, but the overall sentiment was bullish due to
expected strong earnings by Singapore companies. 
</P>
