<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The suspension of sale of
Belgian milk, dairy and chocolate products in Hong Kong imposed
since this June due to the dioxin food crisis in Belgium was
lifted Friday, it was announced by the Hong Kong Department of
Health (DH).
</P>
<P>
However, the suspension of sale of Belgian poultry, eggs, pork,
beef, and related products remains, a Hong Kong DH spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
