<HEADLINE> Three-time French Open Titlist Sanchez-Vicario to Marry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Three-time French Open titlist
Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario of Spain announced on Friday that she will
marry next year.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Sanchez-Vicario will marry with 34-year-old
sports journalist Joan Vehils whom she met four years ago.
</P>
<P>
"We are going to marry before the Sydney Olympics. We would
like that and so would our families," said Sanchez-Vicario.
</P>
<P>
Another Spanish sports star Fernando Escartin also set to marry.
Escartin is Spanish cycling champion who finished third in this
month's Tour de France.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Escartin will marry Ana Ferrer, 29, whom he met
while she was a hostess at a cycling event in October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
