<HEADLINE> China Launches On-line Toy Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- China has formally launched an on-
line toy fair in a bid to increase toy exports, a senior trade
official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Chen Xinhua, vice-minister of foreign trade and economic
cooperation (MOFTEC), said at a press conference that the on-line
fair will cut costs and improve efficiency, and help expand China'
s toy exports as overseas wholesalers begin to place orders for
Christmas toys.
</P>
<P>
The on-line fair, part of the Chinamarket website officially
sponsored by MOFTEC, will offer customers eight categories of
Chinese toys.
</P>
<P>
Toys remain an important export item for China, bringing in 5.
14 billion US dollars last year, about 2.8 percent of China's
overall exports for 1998.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that the Chinamarket website, launched last year, has
realized an initial success. Some 5,000 Chinese firms are
demonstrating nearly 20,000 kinds of Chinese products on the
website, which so far has received a total of 63 million visits
from 122 countries and regions worldwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
