<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Euro Zone Registers Trade Surplus in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The 11-nation euro zone has
registered a trade surplus of 5.4 billion euro (5.67 billion U.S.
dollars) in April this year, Eurostat reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The surplus, however, was down by 2.8 billion euro compared
with the same month a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat gave a total surplus for the January-April period of
15.5 billion euro (16.2 billion dollars) to the zone.
</P>
<P>
It also reported that the 15-nation European Union registered a
trade deficit of 0.7 billion euro (0.73 billion dollars) in April
this year.
</P>
<P>
The EU trade growth with most of its major trade partners was
weak or falling in the first four months of the year, but its
exports to China and Hungary grew by 16 percent.
</P>
<P>
The biggest drop in exports was registered in Russia where EU
exports decreased by 55 percent, followed by a drop in Norway at
10 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
