<HEADLINE> ARATS Rejects SEF's Letter for Violation of "One China" Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Association for Relations
Across the Taiwan Straits (ARATS) rejected a letter from the
Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF) this afternoon for the latter's
violation of the "One China" policy.
</P>
<P>
According to the ARATS, the letter which SEF sent to ARATS at
14:00 today, together with a "negotiation manuscript", has
seriously violated the agreement that "the two sides of the
straits adhere to the 'one China' principle", which was reached in
1992. Therefore, the ARATS refused to accept the letter.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan leader Lee Teng-hui's redefinition of cross-straits
relations as "state-to-state, or at least special state-to-state
relations" on July 9 has strained the cross-straits relations and
aroused indignation worldwide. 
</P>
