<HEADLINE> First China-New Zealand Chartered Flight Opened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The China Southwestern Airlines
today opened the first chartered flight from Beijing, via
Guangzhou or Shanghai, to Auckland, the biggest city of New
Zealand.
</P>
<P>
Passengers on this once-a-week flight are carried by Airbus 340
or Airbus 300 planes,with the flight available on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The flight number will be increased to two every week on
October 1, which are on Tuesday and Friday. The one on Tuesday,
via Guangzhou, covers an one-way air distance of 11,050 kilometers
and takes 13 hours; the other one on Friday, via Shanghai, covers
an one-way distance of 11,500 kilometers and takes 13 hours and 35
minutes.
</P>
<P>
Port Auckland, a commercial and industrial center in New
Zealand, is home to one-third of the country's total population.
</P>
<P>
Insiders said that the chartered flight is expected to play an
important role in prompting the two countries' economic and
culture exchanges, as well as their tourism industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
