<HEADLINE> Beijing Urges to Protect Reservoirs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Beijing approved a regulation
today on the protection of reservoirs in the city which are
threatened by pollution.
</P>
<P>
Sources of the Beijing Municipal People's Congress, or the city
legislature, said that Beijing has two major reservoirs that
provide more than 60 percent of drinking water for the citizens,
and punishment will be imposed to those who pollute them.
</P>
<P>
The new measures include setting up partitions to prevent
people from reaching the Miyun and Huairou reservoirs on Beijing's
suburbs, and prohibiting using mules and horses to carry tourists
to the area.
</P>
<P>
Lack of water has been an headache for the Chinese capital.
</P>
</TEXT>
