<HEADLINE> Person in Changchun Accuses Falun Gong Founder Of Fraud </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A person who got to know Li
Hongzhi, founder of the Falun Gong, around 1992 in Li's hometown
has accused Li of deceiving his followers and taking their money.
</P>
<P>
Liu Fengcai, a 60-year-old journalist in Changchun, the capital
of Jilin Province, told Xinhua that the Falun Dafa was just
nonsense. He says that Li, who founded the Falun Gong cult, an
illegal organization, in 1992, used some sleight of hand and
ambiguous scientific jargons and malicious fallacies to deceive
people.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that he decided to break away from Li after he had
found out that Li was a braggart, a liar, and a swindler, who
promoted Falun Gong with the purpose of defrauding his followers.
Li's malicious fallacies about how the Earth will explode also
caused Liu to sever ties with Li.
</P>
<P>
Liu says that Li concocted Falun Gong to lure more followers
and to get more money from them. Liu estimated that Li had earned
more than one million yuan by 1994 from his lectures, training
classes, and books related to Falun Gong and from donations from
different sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
