<DOCNO> XIE19990730.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yasay Assures Pullout of ECA's Threat on PAL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Securities and
Exchange Commission (SEC) said the European Credit Agency (ECA)
will not withdraw its support for the rehabilitation program of
the Philippine Airlines (PAL), Philippine News Agency reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The assurance was made by SEC Chairman Perfecto Yasay, Jr. in
an interview over reports that ECA was threatening to pullout its
support in PAL, after U.S. Eximbank disagreed to the terms and
conditions set in the PAL's rehabilitation plan.
</P>
<P>
In fact, he said, it is very remote that the agency will do
this considering that it is now supportive of the PAL's
rehabilitation plan.
</P>
<P>
More than this, business tycoon Lucio Tan is finalizing plans
to negotiate for the Eximbank's withdrawal of its objection to the
rehabilitation plan.
</P>
<P>
The PAL's rehabilitation plan prospered after Tan infused 200
million U.S. dollars from his own pockets to revive the
cash-strapped PAL, rather than see the flag-carrier fold up in
history.
</P>
<P>
Eximbank, it was learned, opted to petition in a U.S. court the
reduction of PAL's receivership from seven to only three. And it
demanded that officials comprising of the receiver committee would
be knowledgeable in the rehabilitation of distressed firms in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Yasay said the SEC and the creditors have also agreed not to
allow for the non-voting representative of the airline's secured
creditors into the rehabilitation committee.
</P>
<P>
Instead, Yasay said, they would be given the fullest
opportunity to input ideas on the rehabilitation of PAL and SEC
would also allow the secured creditors to have the opportunity to
protect their rights in the event that there is a material default
in the payment of obligations.
</P>
<P>
But this can only happen if the SEC has determined that the
default payment for PAL is no longer viable, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he expressed confidence that Eximbank is close to
agreeing to the terms and it is hoped that the withdrawal of
Eximbank's objection can be made within a few days.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Tan expressed plans to pull out his 200-million-dollar
investment in PAL on account of the misunderstanding between some
of the creditors and Eximbank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
