<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Launch Fresh Attacks Against Opposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban militia
Friday launched fresh attacks against the rival Northern Alliance
from a fifth frontline north of the capital of Kabul.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here from Kabul said that fierce fighting
between the two Afghan warring factions is continuing.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a spokesman for the Northern Alliance led by
former defense minister Ahmed Shah Masood as saying that fighting
was also heavy at the New Road, 25 kilometers north of Kabul and
towards the east in the Koh-i-Safi mountain range after the
Taliban launched an infantry assault at Ghorband.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban launched their long-awaited summer offensive on
Wednesday in an effort to end the long-running civil war in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The fighting has focused on four fronts to the south of the
Panjsher Valley, the last stronghold of Masood.
</P>
<P>
During the last three days, at least 130 people from the both
sides are reported to have been killed. Meanwhile, four civilians
were killed and more than 10 others injured in rocket attacks by
the Northern Alliance at Kabul. 
</P>
