<HEADLINE> Another Plane Crashes in Philippines Injuring 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A six-seater aircraft crashed into
the sea in the southern Philippines Friday, second one within a
week, Philippine News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The light aircraft plunged into the sea off the southern city
of Davao on the Mindanao Island some 20 minutes after it took off
at the Davao International Airport for a test flight.
</P>
<P>
At l0:24 a.m., the pilot of the ill-fated CESSNA 555 plane
radioed to the airport tower that he was heading for an emergency
landing over Babak, Garden City of Samal Island which is just off
Davao City.
</P>
<P>
Fishermen rescued the three Cessna passengers and brought them
to hospital. Two of them suffered slight injuries but one was
still in serious condition as he almost drowned.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday also witnessed a plane crash in Luzon Island of the
northern Philippines. The two pilots and six passengers have been
confirmed dead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
