<HEADLINE> Tanzania Police Investigating Deaths of 11 Pupils </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian police are
investigating an incident in which 11 pupils were buried alive in
a sand pit and have detained three teachers involved.
</P>
<P>
The pupils, mostly girls, were killed two days ago when they
were digging a hole in the sand to help their school build a
latrine on self- reliance basis, media reports said Friday.
</P>
<P>
They were killed in the two-meter-deep hole when sand collapsed
and covered them, the police said, adding that investigations are
still going on to establish the exact circumstances that led to
their deaths.
</P>
<P>
The students belonged to a primary school in Mufindi District
in southwest region of Iringa.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy shocked the nation, with condolences coming from
President Benjamin Mkapa and Prime Minister Frederick Sumaye.
</P>
</TEXT>
