<HEADLINE> Passenger Arrivals in Macao Rise in 1st Half of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Passenger arrivals in Macao by means
of marine, land and air routes rose 6.2 percent in the first half
of the year over the same period of 1998, the latest official
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
According to recent figures released by the Macao Census and
Statistics Department, the total number of passengers to Macao
reached 3,613,651 in the six months.
</P>
<P>
Particularly in June, passenger arrivals soared 19.4 percent
over the same month of last year.
</P>
<P>
Passengers from Hong Kong, who accounted for 59.2 percent of
the total, dropped 12.6 percent from the same period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
However, those coming from China's inland areas, the Republic
of Korea and South Asian countries showed considerable increases
of 141.6 percent, 49.5 percent and 34.9 percent, respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
