<HEADLINE> Southern China's Beauty Industry Getting Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The beauty industry in the
capital of China's Guangdong Province has begun to appeal to a
number of well-known foreign companies.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss Centre de Revitalization Clinique Lemana recently
joined a Hong Kong company in setting up a chain of beauty parlors
in several luxury hotels in Guangzhou and a large sanitarium with
hairdressing, skincare, and body shaping.
</P>
<P>
It cost 350 million yuan, the largest single foreign investment
in Guangzhou's beauty industry. Denise Pfister, the company's
general manager, says that they have observed that Chinese demand
for skincare and body shaping is increasing as the living standard
improves.
</P>
<P>
She says that the company will introduce state-of-the-art
facilities and techniques from Spain, Italy, and France to satisfy
the Chinese demand for high quality beauty services.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, many chic beauty shops have been appearing on
the streets of the city and are quite popular with their
decorations and stylish services.  
