<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 07:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Shows Ascending Trend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus stock market continued
giant daily leaps amidst investor frenzy during the past week, a
weekly market review said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The review, issued by the Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corporation Limited (CISCO), noted that the Cyprus Stock Exchange
(CSE) closed on Monday and Tuesday in an attempt to clear the huge
backlog that has accumulated due to the massive increase in volume
levels.
</P>
<P>
The market saw a forceful comeback on Wednesday and stunned CSE
players, who watched the daily volume shoot to 70 million Cyprus
pounds (126 million U.S. dollars) and the CISCO All-Share Index to
1,441.40 points, a new all-time high record, while capital
appreciation since year-end was estimated at 217.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The volume of transactions on the same day also constituted a
new daily record and was more than double the previous record,
which had been reached only a few days earlier.
</P>
<P>
The CISCO All-Share Index closed at 1,330.8 points on
Thursday. The daily deviation of the market was minus 110.6 points
or minus 7.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Transactions volume registered a record high this week with
150.1 million pounds (270.2 million dollars) for three trading
sessions, compared to 141.8 million pounds (255.2 million dollars)
of the previous week of five trading sessions.
</P>
<P>
The average daily volume this week reached 50 million pounds
(90 million dollars), as compared to 28.4 million pounds (51.1
million dollars) the week before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
