<HEADLINE> Wang Lianying Doubtful for Title Defence at Military Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- China's five-time world champion
Wang Lianying is doubtful for her title defence in military
pentathlon at the Military World Games in Zagreb, Croatia, next
month because of an injury.
</P>
<P>
"I have not trained for weeks," said Wang on Friday. "Whether I
will compete at Zagreb will depend on how well I recover. If not,
I will just try my best to do some logistic work for my teammates.
"
</P>
<P>
Wang injured her right calf muscles during training one month
ago and could only manage mild excercises now.
</P>
<P>
Her injury also dealt a blow to China's defence of the event's
team title at the August 8-17 games.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the 30-year-old major won her fifth consecutive world
pentathlon championship to become the first woman to achieve such
a feat in the history.
</P>
<P>
Four years ago at the inaugural Military World Games in Rome,
Italy, she won the individual title and was a member of the
champion team.
</P>
<P>
China is sending 145 athletes to the Zagreb games and hopes to
grab at least 13 gold medals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
