ROME -- Italian Police have tracked down an international
enriched uranium-trafficking ring and arrested more than a dozen
of its members in Rome and Palermo, capital of Sicily,on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In March 1998, policemen who disguised as uranium buyers
penetrated into the ring, leading to the recovery of one 10-
kilogram ingot of enriched uranium and the arrest of 15 suspects.
