<HEADLINE> Mexico Beats Bolivia 1-0 in Confederations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Francisco Palencia scored a
header in the 51st minute, leading Mexico past Bolivia into the
semifinals at the Confederations Cup Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
Finishing the first round at the top of Group A, Mexico will
play against the second placer from Group B on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Mexicans have created many chances but the golden goal came
in the 51st minute when Palencia took advantage of a corner kick
to score with a header.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Thursday, Saudi Arabia beat Egypt 5-1. The Mexicans'
victory also sent the Saudis to the semifinals. They will play the
top team from group B. Egypt and Bolivia were eliminated from the
tournament. 
</P>
