<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 13 Species of Wild Animals Extinct in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen out of 903 species of wild
animals in Bangladesh are extinct and 200 others are threatened,
according to a red book on threatened animals.
</P>
<P>
The book, prepared by the International Union for Conservation
of Nature and Natural Resources, Bangladesh, will be published
next month in five volumes in both Bangla and English, the
Independent daily newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Out of the total wild animals, data was deficient on 342
species, and 348 other species were not threatened, researchers
who prepared the book were quoted as stating.
</P>
<P>
The 342 animals on which data was deficient might include some
species that are already extinct or are threatened, they
cautioned.
</P>
<P>
The study based on published materials and recent observation
of experts and researchers has listed five genera of animals --
fishes, amphibians, reptiles, birds and mammals -- and has shown
that out of the species that are extinct one is reptile, two are
birds and 10 mammals.
</P>
<P>
The aim of compiling the book is to create awareness among the
people in advance so that they took necessary conservation and
restoration measures.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the red book also includes a brief write-up on the
description, habitats, distribution, threats, conservation status,
conservation need and extra-territorial distribution of every
threatened species. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
