<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With World Food Program Director </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIDAIHE, July 30 (Xinhua)-- President Jiang Zemin, in a
meeting today with the executive director of the World Food
Program (WFP) Catherine Bertini, spoke highly of the WFP's efforts
to provide grain aid to developing countries in the past.
</P>
<P>
He discussed China's program to lift people out of poverty and
expressed his appreciation for the WFP's cooperation with China.
He also thanked the WFP for emergency aid to 4 Chinese provinces
along the Yangtzi River that were hit by floods last year and said
he hopes that the cooperation with the WFP can be reinforced to
eradicate poverty in China.
</P>
<P>
Bertini praised China's achievements in agricultural
development and expressed satisfaction with the implementation of
the WFP aid project in China.
</P>
<P>
She said the WFP is pleased to work with the Chinese government
to help those Chinese who are suffering from the catastrophic
flood and voiced concern for the current flood situation in China.
She told Jiang that she will continue to work for a closer
cooperative relationship with China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
