<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 30 (Xinhua) -- China and the Republic of Korea (
ROK) are expected to have rapid growth in tourism this year,
according to a high-ranking ROK tourism executive.
</P>
<P>
Kim Yong Il, vice-president of the Korea National Tourism
Organization, predicts that about a million tourists from ROK are
expected to visit China this year and some 300,000 Chinese
tourists will go to tour the ROK.
</P>
<P>
He said exchanges with China have been on rise since the two
countries established diplomatic ties in 1992. The number of
visitors from both countries reached 720,000 last year compared
with 1992's 200,000.
</P>
<P>
His organization has a representative office in Beijing and is
considering opening one in east China's Shanghai municipality to
expand its business in China. The ROK has also decided to simplify
visa procedures for Chinese visitors as of August 1 and has
designated September as ROK-China Tourism Month. Tourism
departments and services and airline companies in the ROK have
been active in promoting tourism exchanges between the two
countries.  
