<HEADLINE> Beijing Seminar Held To Criticize Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Two Beijing newspapers, People's
Daily and Guangming Daily, held a seminar on Thursday to criticize
Falun Gong and expose its dangers.
</P>
<P>
Participants said that Falun Dafa, which was developed by Li
Hongzhi, goes against modern science and civilization and the
drive to build socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The illegal Falun Gong organization has done great harm to
society, they said, and the ugliness of its motives, the
strictness of its organization, and the absurdity of its preaches
are shocking and the country will have endless troubles if it is
not banned and thoroughly exposed.
</P>
<P>
Yang Muzhi, the deputy director of the State Press and
Publication Administration, said that Li's Doomsday idea is the
theoretical basis of his milicious fallacies, and that he says
nothing new and embodies the denial of the real world and has
strong anti-social and anti-government tendencies,
</P>
<P>
Professor Zhu Bokun of Beijing University said that Falun Gong
is actually a superstitious secret society under the guise of
qigong and physical exercise and has harmed a lot of people's
bodies and minds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
