<HEADLINE> China's Air Force Trains Better Pilots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- China's Air Force has made
untiring efforts to train better pilots, recruiting from military
academies and non-military colleges and is exploring new ways of
training people with master's degrees.
</P>
<P>
The larger proportion of high-caliber pilots has improved the
air force's combat effectiveness, sources say, and as a result,
the air force has made tremendous progress in tactical training
and maneuvers under different weather conditions.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the air force has placed the same importance
on improving weaponry and training qualified personnel to adapt
itself to modern warfare, they say.
</P>
<P>
China's military academies are playing a significant role in
training these personnel and have been successful in research on
warfare and military techniques.
</P>
<P>
In introducing a postdoctoral program in its engineering
institutes, the air force has also doubled the number of military
academies that are authorized to award master's and doctor's
degrees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
