<HEADLINE> Ukraine Condemns Killing of Serbs in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine on Thursday condemned the
latest killing of 14 Serbs in Yugoslavia's Kosovo province and
demanded those responsible for the slayings be brought to justice
as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
A statement released by the Foreign Ministry said the tragedy
on July 23 proved again that the deep-rooted racial conflicts
there had already turned persistent and full-scale.
</P>
<P>
Only with long-term and unremitting efforts by the entire
international community, international organizations, power organs
and ethnic groups, could this conflict be stopped, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
It noted that the reconciliation in the Balkan countries could
not be achieved until the successful implementation of the U.N.
related resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Bodies of 14 Serbs were found in Brako village, south of
Pristina, on July 23 in the last rage of ethnic conflicts in the
troubled province of Kosovo. 
</P>
