<HEADLINE> Shanghai Management College For Automobile Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Tongji University in Shanghai has
set up a management college for the automobile industry in
cooperation with the Shanghai Automobile Group, one of China's
largest automobile manufacturers and producer of the Santana.
</P>
<P>
The institute is China's first. It will mainly provide
professional training for the group's employees to help them learn
more about sales and management.
</P>
<P>
It will also do business surveys for the auto market and
research on what customers want to improve products.
</P>
<P>
The college has been provided with advanced facilities like a
multi-media computer system, laboratories, and a simulated auto
market. 
