<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan President Condemns Assassination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga has unreservedly condemned the cruel assassination of
Neelan Thiruchelvam and called on the people to embrace the vision
of ethnic harmony and peace that he was committed to.
</P>
<P>
In her message of condolence issued Thursday night, the
president said the aim of terrorists who seek to decimate such
eminent and democratic intellectuals of rare quality is to
establish the terrorist leadership of the Tamil rebels as the only
valid leaders of the Tamil people.
</P>
<P>
Thiruchelvam, vice-president of the Tamil United liberation
Front (TULF) and a parliamentarian, was killed instantly Thursday
morning in a suicide bombing attack at a stone's throw from his
home in Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The bomber jumped off the back of a motor cyclist and onto
Thiruchelvam's car as it approached a busy intersection.
</P>
<P>
The president said Thiruchelvam had won the affection and
respect of not only the Tamil-speaking people but also all the
communities in the country.
</P>
<P>
He was a distinguished academic who had earned the plaudits of
a broad spectrum of the international community, the president
noted in her message.
</P>
<P>
"Knowing fully well the threats and dangers to his life, he
carried on an untiring and inestimable effort through many years
to find solutions to the ethnic crisis that we continue to face,"
she said.
</P>
<P>
However, the president added that savage assassinations of this
type only help underline the fact that in order to obtain the true
 rights and freedoms of the Tamil people, it is necessary to have
more leaders of the caliber of Thiruchelvam, who have respect for
the rights of man. 
</P>
</TEXT>
