<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Striker Kurniawan Fails Doping Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's best striker Kurniawan
Dwi Yulianto has made hot news again after his failure in the pre-
competition doping tests conducted by the National Sports Council
(KONI) just prior to the Southeast Asian (SEA) Games.
</P>
<P>
SEA Games training director Imron Z.S. said that Kurniawan, 23,
tested positive for amphetamines after KONI and the Jakarta doping
laboratory conducted the tests in June and this month.
</P>
<P>
"KONI decided to ban Kurniawan from competing in Brunei. I have
contacted the secretary-general of the All-Indonesian Soccer
Federation (PSSI) and told him to find a substitute otherwise the
national team should play with the remaining 17 players," he said.
</P>
<P>
The national soccer team left Indonesia for Brunei on July 27
as it must prepare for its first match in Group B against Cambodia
on Saturday. KONI withheld Kurniawan's passport and ticket in
order to prevent him from leaving the country.
</P>
<P>
"Two members of the soccer team tested positive for the
substance in the first test. I informed PSSI chairman Agum Gumelar
and its officials, asking them to get them cleaned up in the
remaining six weeks. I didn't know Kurniawan was addicted to the
substance," he said, refusing to name the other player.
</P>
<P>
"Kurniawan also failed the second test on July 22, but I'm not
immediately taking stern action against him. I first had to tell
the PSSI chairman the results," he was quoted by the Jakarta Post
Friday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Amphetamines, which is included as a banned substance on the
doping list, is usually used to reduce weight and to relieve
depression.
</P>
<P>
Kurniawan declined to comment on the matter when visited by
reporters in his room in Hotel Atlet Century Park in Senayan.
</P>
<P>
PSSI secretary-general Noegraha Besoes said PSSI was awaiting a
second opinion on the tests from the federation's medical team of
Dr. Moh. Nasrun and Dr. Supriyantoro.
</P>
<P>
Agum is expected to announce the results to the public soon.
</P>
<P>
"I have received the test results from KONI and reported to the
chairman, and he told me to recheck. So we set up the medical team.
This is not a small problem," he said.
</P>
<P>
Noegraha said the decision of whether to send Kurniawan to the
Games remained with KONI only if tests by PSSI's medical team were
negative. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
