<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Fall Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 29 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange
closed sharply down at 5,267.69 on Thursday with the benchmark IPC
index falling 267.69 points, or 3.94 percent.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the decline was influenced by falling stock
prices in the United States and Brazil because of a possible
increase in the federal reserve interest rate.
</P>
<P>
Operators changed 106.11 million shares for about 120.06
million U.S. dollars on Thursday against 84.25 million shares at a
value of 152.20 million dollars on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican currency peso stood at 9.60 to one dollar for sale
and 9.25 for purchase in the main exchange house in the Mexican
capital, compared with 9.50 for sale and 9.20 for purchase on
Wednesday. 
