Hongzhi, founder of Falun Gong, is a struggle which has an
important bearing on the fundamental faith of communists, on the
ideological basis for uniting the Chinese people, and on the
destiny and future of the Communist Party and the government," it
says, "it is a political struggle in the ideological sphere about
winning over the broad masses of people."
</P>
<P>
Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- Officials and people from all walks of life of the country
voiced their opinions stressing that they will not allow the great
achievements made in China's construction of socialist legal
system to be damaged by Falun Gong or other superstitious
activities.
</P>
<P>
Many said that they will never allow Li Hongzhi and the illegal
Falun Gong attempts to destroy the building of China's socialist
legal system.
</P>
<P>
Police officers in Tianjin Municipality said that preventing
Falun Gong practitioners from receiving medical treatment in
hospitals impinges on people's rights, and the siege of news media
units and governmental departments violate legal regulations on
demonstrations.
</P>
<P>
-- A commentary released by the Xinhua News Agency warns the
Taiwan authorities against playing tricks on relations between the
two sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- Every means should be employed to ensure the growth of
exports and foreign direct investment in China, State Councilor Wu
Yi urged at the national mid-year conference on foreign trade and
economic cooperation held in Beijing from July 27 to 28.
</P>
<P>
Both China's exports and foreign direct investment dipped
during the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
-- The Ministry of Public Security has issued a wanted notice
for the arrest of Li Hongzhi, head of the "Falun Dafa Research
Society" and his Falun Gong organizations. 
</P>
