<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudis Rout Egyptians in Confederations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arbia raised its hopes
of entering the semifinals as it recorded a convincing victory
over Egypt 5-1 in the Confederations Cup here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Marzouk Al Otaibi scored four goals with Ibrahim Al Shahrani
added the other in the 63rd minute.
</P>
<P>
By exploiting Egypt's weak defense, Al Otabi scored the opener
in the seventh minute and added the second in the 33rd minute for
a 2-0 lead at half break.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptians responded with rough play, which led to three
expulsions, and only netted their lone goal through penalty kick
by Ibrahim Samir in the 69th minute.
</P>
<P>
With only nine Egyptian players left on the field, Al Otaibi
added goals in the 77th and 84th minutes.
</P>
<P>
The game virtually eliminated Egypt's chances for the
semifinals, while gave hope to Saudi Arabia, which lost 5-1 to
Mexico in its opener of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Mexico and Bolivia were to play later Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
