<HEADLINE> U.S. Cyclist Sets Pan Am Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Dylan Casey of the United
States improved his own Pan American record to cycle to the men's
4,000m individual pursuit title here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old national champion from California clocked four
minutes 29.513 seconds to secure the gold, ripping almost two
seconds off the previous best mark of 4:32.118 set up by himself
in yesterday's preliminaries.
</P>
<P>
Argentine Walter Perez took the silver with a time of 4:31.642
and Colombian Marlon Perez Arango the bronze at 4:34.823.
</P>
<P>
Casey began his cycling career in 1993, when he clinched the
first place at the National Collegiate Road Cycling Championships.
He placed eighth in last year's World Track Championship
individual pursuit competition. 
</P>
