<BODY>
<HEADLINE> URGENT  Atlanta Gunman Commits Suicide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 29 (Xinhua) -- The gunman, who was suspected
of killing up to 12 people in Atlanta, committed suicide on
Thursday,Atlanta Mayor Bill Campbell said.
</P>
<P>
At least nine people were killed and 12 others wounded as the
gunman, identified as 44-year-old Mark Barton, opened fire in an
office building in Atlanta City of Georgia State in the United
States Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Three relatives of Barton were found dead at an apartment in
Stockbridge, a town 26 kilometers southeast of Atlanta where
Barton lived, police said.
</P>
<P>
The gunman killed himself a few hours later Thursday after
being pulled over by police at a suburban gas station, Campbell
said.
</P>
<P>
It was the latest in a grim wave of mass shootings at schools
and workplaces and was among the worst office massacres ever in
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Campbell said four of the fatalities were in the office
building and five in another across the street.
</P>
<P>
"It's a terrible tragedy for our city," Campbell said.
</P>
<P>
Barton, a chemist, walked into a brokerage office at Securities
Center in the upscale Buckhead section north of downtown Atlanta
about 3 p.m. summer time (2100 GMT), opened fire, then walked
across the street and began shooting at another brokerage firm
there, the mayor said.
</P>
<P>
Seven of the injured were in critical condition at the trauma
center of Grady Hospital in the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
