<HEADLINE> Argentine, Brazilian Presidents to Discuss Trade Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President Carlos Menem
will travel to Brazil on Thursday after attending a conference in
the United States, to discuss with his Brazilian counterpart
Fernando Cardoso the recent trade crisis between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Argentina and Brazil grew tense after Buenos
Aires announced on July 22 restrictions over imports from Brazil,
involving textile and steel products, electric appliances, paper
and shoes.
</P>
<P>
Brazil protested Argentina's protectionist decision, saying it
lacks reason and calling for an extraordinary meeting on August 4
in Montevideo, Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
President Cardoso said on Wednesday that he believed Argentina
will revise its decision to solve this trade disagreement.
