<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0040 GMT, July 30 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Prime Minister Sergei Stepashin said here
Thursday that his country must become "an equal member of the
European Union" and called for the lifting of restrictions in
trade and economics.
</P>
<P>
Stepashin made the statement at a press conference following
his meeting with Finnish Prime Minister Paavo Lipponen and EU
Foreign Affairs Commissioner Hans Van den Broek.
</P>
<P>
He stressed, "Russia must participate on equal conditions in
all economic projects on liquidating the aftermath of the Yugoslav
crisis," the Itar-Tass news agency reported. (Russia-EU-Ties)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan Thursday
drew the world's attention to the growing poverty and urged the
international community to do more to address the trend.
</P>
<P>
The number of people living in absolute poverty has
substantially increased in the past decade with 3 billion poor
people in the world today, he told a human development forum at
the U.N. headquarters in New York. (UN-Annan-Poverty)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The U.N. Food and Agriculture Organization (
FAO) Thursday issued a special alert to locusts infestations into
areas of Russia from Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Locust swarms have also spread into Uzbekistan and Kyrgyzstan,
said the FAO.
</P>
<P>
