</P>
<P>
ROME -- The Italian cabinet Thursday evening approved a reform
that will eventually cut the number of ministries from eighteen to
twelve.
</P>
<P>
The reform will be made by incorporating some ministries into
others, merging some with others, and getting rid of some.
</P>
<P>
No changes are envisaged for the interior, foreign, justice,
agriculture and defense ministries. (Italy-Ministries-Cut)
</P>
