<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Advances in Generali Open in Austria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov
struggled to sail through the third round at the Generali Open in
Kitzbuehel, Austria on Thursday, keeping alive his hopes of
regaining the world number one spot by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The Russian world number four, who topped the rankings for six
weeks earlier this year, recovered from a disastrous first set to
beat 16th seeded Spaniard Alberto Martin 1-6, 6-4 and 6-3.
</P>
<P>
But second seeded Slovak Karol Kucera went out 7-6, 6-4 to
Austrian Stefan Koubek, who is expected by many to follow in the
footsteps of compatriot and former number one Thomas Muster.
</P>
<P>
Koubek, who captured his first ATP win in Atlanta this year,
will next meet Brazilian Fernando Meligeni who eliminated French
Open finalist Andrei Medvedev 6-1, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Third-seed Alex Corretja also bowed out 6-4, 6-4 to fellow
Spaniard Fernando Vicente.
</P>
<P>
Australian Open champion Kafelnikov will next meet Australia's
Richard Fromberg, who ousted Spaniard Julian Alonso 5-7, 6-3, 7-5.
</P>
