<HEADLINE> Three European Records Broken at Euro Swimming Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Three European records were broken
on Thursday at the 24th European Swimming Championship in Istanbul,
the largest city of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
At the Atakoy Olympic Natatorium in Istanbul, Stephan Perrot of
France broke the men's 200-meter breaststroke European record by
winning the title in 2:12.46.
</P>
<P>
His winning time surpassed British Nick Gillingham's record of
2:12.49. Russian Dmitri Komornikov finished second in 2:12.88 and
French Johann Bernard third in 2:12.96.
</P>
<P>
Inge de Bruijin of the Netherlands set a European record in the
women's 100-meter freestyle race by clocking 58.92 seconds to
shave one-hundreth of a second off Swede Johanna Sjoberg's 58.93
previous mark set on July 2 at the Swedish national championship
in Halmstad.
</P>
<P>
German Stev Theloke timed 25.66 seconds to break the men's 50-
meter backstroke record.
</P>
<P>
In other swimming actions, Yana Klochkova touched home in 2:14.
02 to take the women's 200-meter individual medley, Romanian
Beatrice Caslaru finished second at a time of 2:15.12 and German
Sabine Klenz third with 2:16.95.
</P>
<P>
German Hannah Stockbauer took the women's 800m freestyle in her
winning time of 8:33.79, beating Dutch woman Kirsten Vlieghuis to
second in 8:35.19 and German Jana Henke third in 8:37.06.
</P>
<P>
French Franck Esposito clocked 1:57.20 to triumph in the men's
butterfly final with Ukranian Denys Sylantyev finished second in 1:
57.29 and Russian Anatoly Polyakov third in 1:57.89.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Elena Zhupina and Anna Sorokina of Ukraine won the
three-meter springboard synchronized diving title by 285.15 points,
beating Germans Conny Schmalfuss and Simona to second on 281.10
points. 
</P>
