<HEADLINE> Argentine Stock Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 29 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index of
the Buenos Aires Stock Exchange went up by 0.47 percent to 471.73
points on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 31.334 million U.S. dollars against 21.591
million dollars on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The annual interbank rate of interest stood at 5.5 percent in
the 24-hour term. The peso parity against the dollar was unchanged
at 0.997 for purchase and 1.002 for sale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
