<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Death Toll in U.S. Gunman Shooting Reaches 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 29 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 people were killed
and 12 others wounded as a gunman opened fire in an office
building in Atlanta City of Georgia State in the United States
Thursday, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
It was the latest in a grim wave of mass shootings at schools
and workplaces and was among the worst office massacres ever in
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Atlanta Mayor Bill Campbell said several witnesses recognized
the gunman, identified as Mark Barton, 44.
</P>
<P>
Campbell said four of the fatalities were in the office
building and five in another across the street.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, three relatives of Barton were found dead at an
apartment in Stockbridge, a town 26 kilometers southeast of
Atlanta where Barton lived, police said.
</P>
<P>
"It's a terrible tragedy for our city," Campbell said.
</P>
<P>
Barton, a chemist, walked into a brokerage office at Securities
Center in the upscale Buckhead section north of downtown Atlanta
about 3 p.m. summer time (2100 GMT), opened fire, then walked
across the street and began shooting at another brokerage firm
there, the mayor said.
</P>
<P>
Seven of the injured were in critical condition at the trauma
center of Grady Hospital in the city.
</P>
<P>
A widespread search was launched for Barton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
