<HEADLINE> U.S. Conducts 108 Air Strikes in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 29 (Xinhua) -- The United States, showing off
its military threat, said on Thursday that it had bombed Iraq for
108 times since the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
Of that total, 43 strikes were conducted in the southern no-fly
zone and 65 in northern Iraq, aimed at destroying Iraqi
surface-to-air missile sites, communications sites, and other
military sites, Pentagon spokesman Rear Admiral Craig Quigley told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
In the past couple of days U.S. and British warplanes struck
ytargets in both the southern and northern no-fly zones and eight
people were killed and 26 injured, according to Iraq's news media.
</P>
<P>
The no-fly zones in the southern and northern parts of Iraq
were imposed by the United States and Britain right after the
Gulf War in 1991. But Iraq never recognize the imposed no-fly
zones and has announced any Western warplanes invading its air
space would be deemed violation of its sovereignty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
